  "text": "During the first 10 Myr of the Cenozoic (Palaeocene, approx. 66-56 Ma) the mammalian communities depict generally uniform environments over the entire area of western North America. We therefore focus on the time interval 56 -23 Ma, when major reorganization of topography would have affected western North American habitats, as well as atmospheric circulation and precipitation patterns (figure 2; see also [15, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ).",
